1042","1040":"1040","1060":"1060","Cir 1060":"1060","1114":"1114","1015":"1015","1045":"1045","about 1042":"about 1042","about 1045":"about 1045","about 1022":"about 1022","1108":"1108","Le Havre, Normandie, France":"Le Havre, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France","Saint Jean-d'Abbetot, Seine-Maritime, Haute Normandie, France":"Saint-Jean-d'Abbetot, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France","Normandy, France":"Normandy, France","Saint-Jean-d'Abbetot, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France":"Saint-Jean-d'Abbetot, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Ponthieu","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French: variant of <b>Ponthieu</b>, a habitational name from Ponthieu, a region (former county) in Picardy, between the rivers Authie and Somme."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes de Ponthieu was born about 1022, in Le Havre, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France. She had at least 3 sons with Almeric d'Abitot - 1st Baron de Salwarpe, Viscount de Worcestershire, Châtelain de Worcester et Constable in the King's Household. She died about 1060, in her hometown, at the age of 40, and was buried in Le Havre, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France."},"et":{"about 1022–about 1060":"umbes 1022–umbes 1060","1015–1066":"1015–1066","1040–1108":"1040–1108","1042–1097":"1042–1097","1045–1114":"1045–1114","1022–1060":"1022–1060","about 1060":"umbes 1060","1022":"1022","1066":"1066","1097":"1097","1042":"1042","1040":"1040","1060":"1060","Cir 1060":"1060","1114":"1114","1015":"1015","1045":"1045","about 1042":"umbes 1042","about 1045":"umbes 1045","about 1022":"umbes 1022","1108":"1108","Le Havre, Normandie, France":"Le Havre, Seine-Maritime, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Saint Jean-d'Abbetot, Seine-Maritime, Haute Normandie, France":"Saint-Jean-d'Abbetot, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Saint-Jean-d'Abbetot, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France":"Saint-Jean-d'Abbetot, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1022–about 1060":"noin 1022–noin 1060","1015–1066":"1015–1066","1040–1108":"1040–1108","1042–1097":"1042–1097","1045–1114":"1045–1114","1022–1060":"1022–1060","about 1060":"noin 1060","1022":"1022","1066":"1066","1097":"1097","1042":"1042","1040":"1040","1060":"1060","Cir 1060":"1060","1114":"1114","1015":"1015","1045":"1045","about 1042":"noin 1042","about 10